"manifest_stream_number": 0, "is_dash_periods": true, "protocol": "https", "video_ext": "mp4", "audio_ext": "none", "abr": 0, "vbr": 1770.695, "resolution": "1080x1920", "aspect_ratio": 0.56, "filesize_approx": 2611775, "http_headers": {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/143.0.0.0 Safari/537.36", "Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format": "dash-791017110754446v - 1080x1920 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by telcier", "description": "🎬 Crazy, Stupid, Love.\n2011 ‧ Rom-Com/Dramedy ‧ Film\n📜 Storyline\n*Crazy, Stupid, Love.* is a masterclass in the modern ensemble romantic comedy, weaving together multiple generations of heartbreak and infatuation in Quahog—wait, no, in suburban Los Angeles. The story centers on Cal Weaver, a middle-aged man whose \"perfect\" life shatters when his wife Emily admits to an affair and asks for a divorce. Lost in the world of singlehood, Cal is taken under the wing of Jacob Palmer, a suave, high-stakes womanizer who transforms him from a doting dad into a confident player. However, the film is much more than a simple makeover story; it explores the messy, interconnected lives of Cal's children, Jacob’s unexpected encounter with the fiery Hannah, and the realization that \"soulmates\" aren't just a fairy tale. It is compelling because of its sharp wit, genuine emotional stakes, and a legendary third-act twist that brings every subplot crashing together in a hilariously chaotic backyard brawl.\n\n🎞️ Title Info\n * 📚 Origin: Original screenplay by Dan Fogelman\n * 📅 Release date: July 29, 2011\n * 📺 Runtime: 1 hour 58 minutes\n * 👤 Directors: Glenn Ficarra and John Requa\n * 🖊️ Writer: Dan Fogelman\n * 🎙️ Main cast: Steve Carell, Ryan Gosling, Julianne Moore, Emma Stone, Analeigh Tipton, Jonah Bobo, and Kevin Bacon\n * 🌎 Original language: English (Available on major streaming platforms worldwide)\n * 🎼 Music by: Christophe Beck and Nick Urata\n * ⭐ IMDb rating: 7.4/10\n * 🍅 Rotten Tomatoes score: 79% (Critics) / 78% (Audience)\n * 🧠 Themes: Love, infidelity, masculinity, adolescence, and the search for \"the one\"\n * 🏆 Legacy: Regarded as one of the best rom-coms of the 2010s; it solidified the incredible on-screen chemistry between Ryan Gosling and Emma Stone.\n📺 Where to Watch\nYou can stream *Crazy, Stupid, Love.* globally on platforms like Netflix, Max, and Hulu depending on your region. In India, you can find it available for streaming on Netflix or rent/buy it via Amazon Prime Video and Apple TV.\n\n#CrazyStupidLove #RyanGosling #EmmaStone #SteveCarell #RomCom MovieClassic\n🔔 Follow @telcier for more content like this!\n💌 DM for credit or removal requests", "duration": 11.8, "timestamp": 1776498010, "uploader_id": "80184519956", "uploader": "telcier", "channel": "telcier", "like_count": -1, "comment_count": 173, "comments": [{"author": "pluvio.philia_", "author_id": "68008631866", "id": "18179475955393557", "text": "We sensoring Job now?🥀", "timestamp": 1778680646}, {"author": "dani.evko", "author_id": "71903587155", "id": "17941074753027445", "text": "sir you're applying to clean cow shit", "timestamp": 1778656303}, {"author": "ethan_anderson_777", "author_id": "56846951706", "id": "17891301141471211", "text": "Jesus loves you", "timestamp": 1778633488}, {"author": "kkcclassroom", "author_id": "75029122707", "id": "18584462053046197", "text": "😂😂", "timestamp": 1778626957}, {"author": "kimicall49", "author_id": "5525284537", "id": "18121731193725888", "text": "Hired on the spot 🔥🔥🔥🔥", "timestamp": 1778625674}, {"author": "partha.gg", "author_id": "8452435292", "id": "18066906254352609", "text": "", "timestamp": 1778616770}, {"author": "partha.gg", "author_id": "8452435292", "id": "18163324654379537", "text": "", "timestamp": 1778616755}, {"author": "partha.gg", "author_id": "